{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, fine-tuning ChatGPT for specific tasks still requires uploading data to a central server, which also raises privacy concerns 22.",
    "In contrast, open-source LLMs are free of charge and can be locally fine-tuned for specific tasks within each healthcare institution's secure confines 18.",
    "Previous studies predominantly focused on electronic health records 13, 16 and chest X-rays (CXR) 13, 18 have highlighted the potential of using LLMs to summarize in clinical text.",
    "In contrast, echo-related studies were mainly on data extraction or classification, rather than report summarization [23] [24] [25].",
    "Tang et al."
  ]
}